text: Frazier (also known as Frazer) is an unincorporated community in Buchanan County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Frazer was established in 1871, and remained in operation until 1936. The community has the name of a local family. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Buchanan County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Frazier, Missouri
